snippet.authorDisplayName: This is how the truth dies
snippet.textDisplay:
The Walking Dead fell too in love with the premise of killing off it's important characters. This proved to be a serious problem when they were replaced by cardboard cutouts that the viewers aren't really invested in. I would argue that in a serialized TV premise, having good characters is more important than even having a good script.
Make a character real then make them interesting and then give them something to do, in that order.
